HEADWORD: Forwrap
<hw>For*wrap"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To wrap up; to
conceal.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>All mote be said and nought excused, nor hid, nor
<qex>forwrapped</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Foryelde</ent>⟦br⟧
